7.2.1.3  Planned Nuclear Forces
As a result of the START II Treaty, the US Department of Defense prepared a  
Nuclear Policy Review, issued on 22 September 1994, which projected US nuclear 
forces in the year 2003 after the treaty provision go into effect. Current 
plans are to have 3500 strategic warheads, 950 non-strategic warheads, and 550 
spares counted as part of the active inventory. 

