1,200t/yr compared.

British report on plutonium holdings for 1995 showed that British Nuclear 
Fuels PLC holds a total 85 tonnes tonnes of civilian plutonium. 54 tonnes are 
owned by UK utilities and 31 tonnes owned by BNFL or its overseas customers. 
Of this 85 tonnes, 39.5t remains in spent fuel. Only 66 kg is listed as being 
in MOX fuel exported, none in MOX stock. All separated plutonium has more than 
15% Pu-240. The military plutonium stockpile consists of 4.5 tonnes held in 
various forms by the UK Atomic Energy Authority.

