<html>
<title>MILNET:  World Events And Indicators - Libya</title>
<center>
<h1>MILNET:  Indicators - Libya</h1>
</center>
<img src="/milnet/rainbar3.gif">
<p>
See <a href="/milnet/travwarn.htm">Travel Warnings</a> and specifically the
travel warning for <a href="http://travel.state.gov/libya.html">Libya</a>
, serve as an excellent real time indicator.
<p>
The following events have taken place in Libya:
<p>
<b>Libya</b>
<dl><dd>
<b>Events</b>
<ul type=disc>
<li>Libyan Prison Erupts in Violence, June 1996: Abu Saleem prison, guards were
seized as hostages, some 100 people killed in the fighting, including guards
and prisoners. 
<li>Libyan Soccor Crowd Riots, July 1996: 8 killed, 39 injured.  Rioters spilled into the streets around the Soccer stadium burning cars and throwing rocks.
<p>
</ul>
<b>Analysis</b>
<ul type=disc>
<li>Expenditures made by Libyan Government (essentially by Mohamar Khadaffi)
have really pissed the citzenery off.
<li>Khaddaffi has authorized the shooting on sight of dissedents in Libya
<li>Police burned down shops of suspected militants
<li>Four years of UN Sanctions have taken their tole (imposed after the
Libyan government refused to turn over men suspected of blowing up an 
airliner over Lockerbie, Scotland in 1988 which
killed 270 people.
</ul>
<p>
<b>Possible Indications</b>
<ul type=disc>
<li>Wishful thinking might indicate nationwide rebellion is fulminating in
Libya.
<li>Clearly Khadaffi's rule is showing signs of strain, or more accurately, 
the people appear to be less afraid to show their true feelings.
<li>More political unrest is predicted.
<li>Western nations are likely to take advantage of this unrest and give 
aid to the dissidents in hopes of unseating Khadaffi.
<li>Khadaffi is posed to perform a horrible act of violence, much like
the Chinese government did in the Tinimin Square.
<li>Unfortunately, the government in exile is not thought to be strong 
enough to takeover if Khadaffi falls, so it will be up to Western powers to
bolster any new government.  
<li>Libya requires a strong leader by the nature of the tribal structure 
that Khadaffi has continue to foster despite the rest of the Islamic world's
forward movement.
<li>More indicators will follow before we see clear signs of Khadaffi's fall.
</ul>
<p>
</dl>
<p>
<img src="/milnet/rainbar3.gif">
<br>
<a href="mailto:milnet@onestep.com"><i>milnet@onestep.com</i></a><br>
</html>

</DOC>
