<html>
<title>MILNET:  World Events And Indicators - Colombia</title>
<center>
<h1>MILNET:  Indicators - Colombia</h1>
</center>
<img src="/milnet/rainbar3.gif">
<p>
See <a href="/milnet/travwarn.htm">Travel Warnings</a> and specifically the
travel warning for <a href="http://travel.state.gov/colombia_announce3.html">Colombia</a>
, serve as an excellent real time indicator.
<p>
The following events have taken place in Libya:
<p>
<b></b>
<dl><dd>
<b>Events</b>
<ul type=disc>
<li>U.S. revokes travel visa for President Ernesto Samper, thus preventing a 
crucial meeting on drug control between U.S. and Colombian leaders.  Reasons 
given by the U.S. are that Samper is suspected of ties with drug cartels and
that the cartels funded his election campaign.
<li>Well respected Colombian newspaper calls for Samper's resignation.
<p>
</ul>
<b>Analysis</b>
<ul type=disc>
<li>U.S. officials are putting heavy pressure to remove Samper
<li>Local pressure growing as well, as public knowlege of the possible
cartel links spreads.
<li>Despite all that has happened so far, it appears there are pockets of
good will for Samper, as several areas he has visited have come out in 
support of him.
</ul>
<p>
<b>Possible Indications</b>
<ul type=disc>
<li>Like Manual Noriega, Samper may face world court and possibly U.S. 
drug charges
<li>However, unless he loses more popular support there will be enough
support to ensure he has some power base left.
<li>Seems likely the pressure will be successful, and Samper will step 
down, but will probably avoid capture and extredition
<li>Western nations are likely to take advantage of this unrest and give 
aid to the dissidents in hopes of unseating Samper. 
<li>Khadaffi is posed to perform a horrible act of violence, much like
the Chinese government did in the Tinimin Square.
<li>Unfortunately, the government in exile is not thought to be strong 
enough to takeover if Khadaffi falls, so it will be up to Western powers to
bolster any new government.  
<li>Libya requires a strong leader by the nature of the tribal structure 
that Khadaffi has continue to foster despite the rest of the Islamic world's
forward movement.
<li>More indicators will follow before we see clear signs of Khadaffi's fall.
</ul>
<p>
</dl>
<p>
<img src="/milnet/rainbar3.gif">
<br>
<a href="mailto:milnet@onestep.com"><i>milnet@onestep.com</i></a><br>
</html>

