<html><title>state dept. terrorist profiles</title><pre>

       THE TERRORIST PROFILE WEEKLY FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS
      ---------------------------------------------------------


Written Saturday 11-5-94 in a beach house in Maryland.


By Chris DiBona  <a href="mailto:cdibona@mason1.gmu.edu"><i>cdibona@mason1.gmu.edu</i></a>

--------------------------------------------------------

Introduction:

First who I am......
                            
   My name is Chris, I just in October turned 23 years old, I
   work in Washington DC at the US Department of State in two
   different sections of Information Management. I work in both
   the foreign affairs data processing center (FADPC) and in the
   Modernization office. Note that this does not mean that I am
   anything but a slave gopher. 
        
   In my capacity as a wunderkind (I'm modest too.) I got to see
   a lot of the more up to date projects going on in the department.
   One I really liked was the cd rom projects that published the
   foriegn affairs manual (3000 pages at a paper cost of $2000 a 
   set, or a $2 cd-rom.) The same department that published them also
   puts out a foreign affairs CD-Rom with post reports, and annual 
   reports of the department. One of these annual reports is, you
   guessed it, The Profiles of Global Terrorism.

   So, I figured I'd been taking so much info from the net and gaining
   so much benefit from the internet and all its denizens, that I 
   should give something back to it. Thats' what the Terrorist
   Profile Weekly (TPW) is. 

   So I checked with Diplomatice Security and the Counter Terrorism
   folks and they all had no problem with me re-publishing, so
   I started this list up in january.

   By march I had only 150 or so subscribers, not counting the WELL
   who keeps it on its' gopher site. Then two things happened, normal
   growth , friends telling friends and such, and recognition, in
   the pages of The Montreal X-Press and Internet World. 

   So now, Early november, there are 750 subscribers world wide! I
   would like to thank you , my readers for some pretty cool additions
   to my vanity wall. 

   Past that, what follows are the FAQ posed to me. This faq will
   be sent out to all new subscribers. (If I spelled anything wrong,
   please email so I can stave off any furthur embarassment)

   Note also that this list and faq is dedicated to Alison Merrill.

        Your Editor -
                Chris DiBona

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

1)  Where can I get more info?

Not from me basically, I am as much a student of terrorism as all of
you (and probably less than most) In my position at the Department I
don't come in contact with terrorism info, and if I did, I probably
wouldn't be able to talk about it. Your best bet is to call the
state departments main number at (202)647-4000. Ask for the Public
Affairs division. The people there are employed to help you in your
pursuit of information.

2) Can I get in touch with the xxxxx terrorist group through you?

Ah, not quite. If a terrorist group wants contact , they're not
going to bother with me. But if you are a member of a terrorist
group, send me an anonymous email and I'll keep it in mind. I
will republish any opinions from a source, with clarifiers like
"This individual claims to be a member of...... I take no
responsibility for any falsehood therein... blah blah,"

3) Why are these out of date sometimes?

Cause I'm lazy, I'm working from 1992 info, I really am just a cut
and paste type guy from the Profiles. 

4) Do you have a logo for xxxxx terrorist group?

No. Never. Natch. There are some logos in the the publications
"Violence against Americans Abroad" (more on this later) but
I don't have any plans to scan and uuencode these at any time.
One thing to keep in mind, I work , go to school to get my degree
and have a social life. The TPW is a hobby, as I can't devote too
much time to it.

5) Why haven't I recived a profile in xxxx days?

Cause I'm buzy, see the last couple of lines of Question #4.

6) What happens when you run out of groups??

Oops, this actually has already happened, but that's okay. I'm scurrying
up some more profile for me to use. Also, I'm going to begin reporting 
from the pages of "Violence against americans abroad" which tells
us the startling tales of kidnappings, murders and other such things
overseas, this another annual work which I've gotten my hands on.

7) Do you have an index of the profiles?

No, I've been meaning too, I just don't have any real time, maybe over
christmas I'll type one up, but then again..... maybe not. It took me
8 months to put out a FAQ for chrisakes.

8) Where else can I find this info.

>From you local american embassy. From the Well gopher. On CD-Rom in the
Big Green CD, coming out soon. I'll announce it when it releases. The State
Department proper.

9) Anything else ?

Yeah, remember, I make a point of staying detached from the issues that
these groups fight about, that's all. If you see a group which you
sympathize with being treated with little respect in the profiles, remember
please that this is the position of the government and the State Department,
so don't blame the messenger. 

10) Are you sure that's it?

No, actually one more thing , I didn't think that the movies True Lies 
had/has a political agenda. 

------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
Any comments can be directed back to me! <a href="/mailto:cdibona@mason1.gmu.edu"><i>cdibona@mason1.gmu.edu</i></a>
------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


---
endfile</pre></html>
</DOC>
