<TITLE>X-31 Enhanced Fighter Maneuverability Aircraft</TITLE>
<H2>X-31 Enhanced Fighter Maneuverability 
Aircraft</H2>
<UL>
<LI>                        X-31 Enhanced Fighter Maneuverability Aircraft      .
<LI>Wingspan:			               ?
<LI>Length:				?
<LI>Height:				?
<LI>Weight:				?.
<LI>Speed:				?
<LI>Ceiling:				?
<LI>Engines:				?
<LI>Crew:				? 
</UL>
The X-31 is a US Navy technology development aircraft being used to explore the 
maneuverability envelope for new generations of fighter aircraft.  This aircraft has just 
completed its prerequisite high speed taxi tests on October 3rd, and is expectd to begin its 
first flights soon.<P>
The first tesst reached a ground speed of 130 kts and included a nosewheel liftoff to an 8 
degree up-pitch.  The second test featured a 120 kt deployment of the spin chute and it 
jettison.<P>
   				<P>
