<head><title>OneStep Internet Services End User Services - OnSite Web Page</title></head><body>
<center>
<a href="1stephq.htm"><img src="1steplog.gif"></a>
<h2>Your First Step On The Information Super-Highway</h2>
<p>
</center>
<p>
<p>
<h1>OnSite Web Pages</h1>
<h2>Method 4, Your Own, True Domain</h2>
<p>
<nl>
<b>4.</b>  Searching and finding your web page via "http://www.yourname.com/"
</nl>
<p>
Using the URL "www.yourname.com" requires that you register AND operate a domain name server for your registered domain.  We can do that for you, but only if your domain is not being used elsewhere (and actually that will prohibit are getting it registered for you) and you aren't planning to put any of your own computer networks on the Internet in the near future.  
<p>
For example, if your company name is ABC, you might want to have "www.abc.com" as your web page URL.  But if you have computers at your facility, you may want to have an IP address (i.e. something akin to 205.199.11.1) that is used to put your computers on the Internet.  As you can see, we are certainly leaving the realm of personal web pages, and branching into the commercial OnSite web pages.  
<p>
If OneStep Internet Services registers your domain name for you (the "www.abc.com" yields a new domain name of "abc.com"), then from that day forward the Internet will all messages meant for computers of "abc.com" to our servers.  Thus later, this becomes a major pain for both us if you decide to bring your own computers online.
<p>
However, having said this, there is one situation where this is actually just fine.  If you are planning on building a Web Server with us, and then sometime later taking over maintenance and further development, then it only makes sense that our use of your domain name be temporary.  For this situation, we will help you register your domain.
<p>
Since this is a "true" domain registeration, it requires a set of complex transactions between us and the Internet.  These transactions translate into hours of time spent on the project, and we must pass that cost onto you.  
<p>
Therefore, for a "true" domain registeration and domain server setup, we will charge $250.  This is a onetime fee for the setup.  Transfer of the domain will be charged at $50 at the time of the transfer away from a OneStep Internet Services domain server (we assume deleting your domain is easier than getting it running).
<p>
One advantage of this situation is that we can maintain a number of servers for you at our facility.  Addtional name server operations will be charged at $50 per hour, and will include testing and verification of external access as required.
<P>
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<a href="comm_in.onestep.html"><b>Comments/User Survey/Inquiries</b></a>
<p>
<hr>
For more information email to: <address>InServices@onestep.com</address>
</body></html>


