<HTML><TITLE>OneStep Internet Services Provider Services - Do It Yourself Guide</TITLE>
<p>
	            <img src="1steplog.gif">
<p>
<p>
		                  <a href="initial.htm"><img src="serveasy.gif"></a> 
 
 
<H1>OneStep Internet Services Provider Services - Do Your Own Marketing</h1>
<p>
Well its really not THAT hard.  But be prepared to spend time online.  Here's how it works.  You search for topic areas of interest to your customers.  Then vist those areas.  When you find one that is especially suited to your customers, then write the webmaster and see if a link to your Home Page would be possible.  Maybe the other folks would like you to link to them too!  It's a network...so let's use as a network...a network of friends and new friends doing business together.
<p>
<h2>Advertising</h2>
<p>
Advertising on the NET is a strange animal.  The most prevalent method is via EMail.  Like the advertising on your television, this is intrusive.  Word of mouth is better however.  For instance, instead of blasting out a message to everyone, think about compiling a list of Internet contacts.  As this list grows (along with your NET based customer base), then so does your exposure.  This is limited growth, but it beats hitting people over the head!  A good salesman will tell you that qualified leads pay dividends.   Using your search list you created when looking for similar topic areas to your own, make personal Email contact with te contact at the home page you are interested in.  Sometimes all it takes is for you two to find out your doing something similar and BOOM you have a new partner on the NET.
<p>
<H3>Advice</h3>
<p>
OneStep Internet Services would be happy to give you some more specific advice.  Just click on Comments below and we'll contact you after you submit your request.
