<html>
<title>OneStep Internet Services Internet Services</title>
<center>
<a href="/onestep/creative.htm"><img src="server.gif"></a>
<p>
<h1>Logo Services</h1>
</center>
Our Graphics Staff excel in the creation of new Corporate Identities including
the building of a new logo for your enterprise.  Below we list several categories
you need to consider when deciding on a new logo.  Especially important on the 
Internet is the size and number of colors used in your color logo.  For 
example, the size and colors determine how many bytes of data are required to
store the logo, which directly effects how fast the logo can be moved from the
web page to the user's display.  
<p>
Few people will sit still for 1MB image to be
"downloaded" while browsing the Internet.  However, as long as you warn folks
about a large logo, say 140,000 bytes, or better yet give them the option to
not have to wait, then your logo does not become a problem.  
<p>
Also you want to ensure your logo is scaleable.  For instance, the logo could
look fantastic at a 2"x3" size, but once scaled down to .5"X.75", the logo
is undecipherable.  That's unfortunate, because that might be the size you 
need to use on lower pages in the web heirarchy, or perhaps used on your 
letterhead.
<p>
As you can see there are a number of things to consider when creating a logo. The previous
examples are just a few of the important matters that must be discussed when 
devloping a new logo.  But for now we will give you a few examples...both to
show you what we can do, but also to get your own creative processes brewing on
this very important aspect of marketing your company.
<p>
Below are a number of examples or our work.  The possibilities are endless 
however, so if you have an idea of a new logo or want us to create an all new
idea for you, we are ready to help:
<pre>



</pre>
<ul>
<li><img src="1steplog.gif" align=middle> Simple with color text 
<p>
<li><img src="/www2.gif" align=middle> Slightly complex color text
<p>
<li><a href="smpbckex.htm">Simple background</a> with color text (18K bytes)
<li><a href="cmpbckex.htm">Complex background</a> with color text (25K bytes)
<li><a href="phtbckex.htm">Photo background</a> with color text (102K Bytes)
</ul>

<p>
