<title>MILNET:  Travel Advisories - Mirror Copy - Albania</title>
<center>
<p>
<a href="/milnet/milnet.htm"><img src="/milnet/milico.gif" align=middle alt="Mil
net Main"></a>
<a href="/milnet/terror.htm"><img src="/milnet/terror.gif" align=middle alt="Ter
rorism"></a>
<p>
<h1>Albania</h1>
<hr>
<p>
<h2>STATE DEPARTMENT TRAVEL INFORMATION 
</h2>
</center>
<hr>
<b>Albania - Public Announcement</b><br>
May 30, 1996<p>

<p>

U.S. DEPARTMENT OF STATE<br>
Office of the Spokesman<br>
For Immediate Release<p>

Political forces disappointed with the conduct and results of May 26 parliamentary elections in
Albania have called for public demonstrations to protest the elections.  One unapproved
demonstration in central Tirana on May 28 was dispersed by police and resulted in injuries to
participants and bystanders.  The U.S. Embassy in Tirana strongly advises American citizens to
avoid areas where political protests are expected, to leave the area of spontaneous demonstrations
and to avoid any large gatherings of people.<p>
<P>
No. 96-albania<P>
