<title>MILNET:  Travel Advisories - Mirror Copy - Ethiopia</title>
<center>
<p>
<a href="/milnet/milnet.htm"><img src="/milnet/milico.gif" align=middle alt="Mil
net Main"></a>
<a href="/milnet/terror.htm"><img src="/milnet/terror.gif" align=middle alt="Ter
rorism"></a>
<p>
<h1>Ethiopia</h1>
<hr>
<p>
<h2>STATE DEPARTMENT TRAVEL INFORMATION 
</h2>
</center>
<hr>
<b>Ethiopia - Public Announcement</b><br>
 July 18, 1996
<p>
 U.S. DEPARTMENT OF STATE<br>
 Office of the Spokesman<br>
 For Immediate Release<br>
<p>
The U.S. Embassy in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia has issued the following 
warden notice:
<p>
The U.S. Embassy reminds U.S. citizens living and working in 
Ethiopia to pay extra attention to their security in day to day 
activities.  The American Embassy has recently received vague 
threats against the U.S. presence in Ethiopia.  U.S. citizens should 
exercise caution and remain vigilant.  Reports of any suspicious 
activity and any questions should be directed to the Embassy's 
Regional Security Officer.
<p>
 No. 96-eth
<p>
For further information consult the Department's latest Consular 
Information Sheet on <a href="/milnet/travel/ethiopia.htm">Ethiopia</a>.
