<h1>Israel</h1>
<hr>
<p>
<h2>STATE DEPARTMENT TRAVEL INFORMATION
</h2>
</center>
<hr>
<b>Israel - Public Announcement</b><br>
April 12, 1996<p>

U.S. DEPARTMENT OF STATE<br>
Office of the Spokesman<br>
For Immediate Release<p>

On April 12, 1996, the U.S. Embassy in Tel Aviv issued the following announcement to its
personnel:<p>

On April 12, Katyusha rockets were directed against northern Israel.  Most fell on the
"Panhandle" area in the vicinity of Kiryat Shemona.  Precautionary measures have been taken to
evacuate portions of the civilian population.  In view of this and recent events in Lebanon,
American Embassy personnel, for the time being, are advised to avoid:<p>

- The "Panhandle" area of northern Israel (e.g., the Kiryat Shemona, Metulla and the Dan areas).<p>

- Areas north of Nahariya along an east/west line roughly defined by routes 89 and 91.<p>

Previous advice to avoid public bus travel, bus stops, and crowded areas remains in effect.<p>
No. 96-israel4<P>
The Department of State's Public Announcements of March 5 and March 7, 1996 and Consular
Information Sheet on Israel, The Gaza Strip, Jericho Area, and the Territories Occupied and
Administered by Israel of May 22, 1995 remain in effect.<p>
<P>
<p>
For further information consult the Department's latest Consular
Information Sheet on <a href="/milnet/travel/israel.htm">Israel</a>.
