<hr>
<p>
<h2>STATE DEPARTMENT TRAVEL INFORMATION
</h2>
</center>
Israel and the West Bank - Public Announcements<br>
 August 29, 1996<br>
<p>
 U.S. DEPARTMENT OF STATE<br>
 Office of the Spokesman<br>
 For Immediate Release<br>
<p>
On August 29, 1996, the American Consulate General in Jerusalem 
issued the following warden message:
<p>
        "Because we judge that there is an increased possibility of 
demonstrations and disturbances, particularly in the area of the Old 
City of Jerusalem during the weekend of August 30 through September 
1, American citizens are advised to avoid unnecessary travel to the 
Old City of Jerusalem and the West Bank during that time.  We 
believe that U.S. citizens should maintain an awareness of their 
surroundings and monitor local media.  If you are in the vicinity of 
a demonstration, you are advised to depart the area."
<p>
 No. 96-ibw
