<p>
<h1>Israel, Jerusalem, The West Bank and Gaza</h1>
<hr>
<p>
<h2>STATE DEPARTMENT TRAVEL INFORMATION
</h2>
</center>
Jerusalem, the West Bank and Gaza - Public Announcement<br>
 September 26, 1996<br>
<p>
<b>
 U.S. DEPARTMENT OF STATE<br>
 Office of the Spokesman<br>
 For Immediate Release<br>
</b>
<p>
Due to ongoing violence in the West Bank and Gaza, American 
citizens are advised to avoid travel to those areas.  Additionally, 
in light of the possibility of demonstrations in the Old City and 
East Jerusalem on Friday, September 27, American citizens are 
advised to avoid those areas on that day.  After that day, Americans 
who must travel in the Old City of Jerusalem should exercise extreme 
caution.
<p>
The situation in the West Bank and Gaza is volatile.  American 
citizens are advised to monitor the news media to remain well 
informed about the situation.
<p>
This Public Announcement replaces the Public Announcement issued 
September 25, 1996, and will expire on October 31, 1996.

