<HTML>
<TITLE>US Military Force Strengths</TITLE>
<H1>US Military Force Strengths</H1>
The U.S. maintains forces both inside and outside the continental United States.   Force 
strengths are 1990  estimates of the at home strengths as well as forward deployed 
strengths (as in Europe or the Middle East):<P>
<pre>
<b>                                     Forward</b><br>
<b>Service               At Home        Deployed           Total</b><br>       
<HR>US Navy              ~281,000        ~300,000          581,000
<HR>US Air Force         ~366,000        ~200,000          566,000
<HR>US Army              ~481,000        ~300,000          781,000
<HR>US Marine Corps       ~75,000         ~75,000          150,000
<HR>                                                     
Grand Total         1,203,000         875,000        2,078,000



</pre>
<hr>
<h1> </h1>
Note:  The above figures are prior to the drawdown of U.S. forces deemed 
necessary in light of the 
reduction of threat due to the breakup of the former Soviet Union.
<p>
<p>
