<HTML>
<TITLE>Chinese Army</TITLE>
<center>
<img src="milnetsm.gif" align=middle, alt="Milnet">
<p>
<p>
<a href="milnet.htm"><img src="milico.gif" align=middle alt="Milnet Main"></a>
<a href="military.htm"><img src="miltico.gif" align=middle alt="Military"></a>
<p>
<h1>Chinese Army</h1>
</center>
Note:  China Military information dried up in the 1985 timeframe.  Subsequently, the "massacre in Tinimen Square" served to 
further isolate China from the western world, and little verifiable data has been available, and what data appears in public form 
appears to be quite similar to verified data in 1983 and thus shows little or no growth.  This can hardly be the correct 
information, and is most likley dressed up figures from the past.  We will endeavor to update this data as possible.<P>
From 1982 to 1983, the Chinese Army grew 11.7%, leaving no doubt as their continued path of growth.  With this arms growth 
has come a parallel growth in offers to other countries ot excess <P>
Chinese production overflows, a production geared to make Chinese allies some of the most well armed in the World.  <P>
Looking at the Chinese Army can be frightening.  In 1983 the ground forces topped 3.1 million in uniform, consisting of the 
"main forces" in 11 military regions, and the "local forces" contained in some 29 provinces (which at that time was under 
reorganization).  The main battle forces in 1983 were deployed in some 8 regions of China (North-East; North; North-West; 
West; South-West; South; Center; and East; These forces maintain the following arms:<P>
<B>AFV:</B>  11,450 units conisting of Sov IS-2; heavy  and T-54 tanks used for training (could easily be armed at any 
time); Chinese type 59 and T-69 (modified T-59) main battle tanks; Type -62 light and TYpe-60/63 light amphibious tanks; 
2,800 type 531, Type-55/56 (BTR-40/-156) and -63 APC.<P>
<B>ARTY:</B>  13,800 including type-56 85mm field antitank pieces; 100mm, Type-60 122mm; type-59 130mm towed; ISU-
122/-152 Self propelled guns (thought to be training);Type-66 152mm towed howitzer; Type-54 122mm and Type--56 152mm 
towed; 122mm SP howitzer; <P>
<B>MRL: </B> 4,500 Type-63 12 X 107mm; 40X122mm; 19X130mm BM-13-16 16x132mm, BM-14-16 16x140mm; 
10x180mm and 10x320mm.<P>
<B>ATK:  </B>40mm, 57mm, 90mm Rocket Launchers; 7,800 57mm and 82mm Recoilless; Type -55 57mm and Type-54 
76mm guns; and Saggar <B>ATGW</B><P><B>
</B><B>AA:  </B>15,000 Type-63 37mm (some twin SP) Type-59 57 mm; Type-56 85mm and Type-59 100mm guns. <P>
<hr>
