<HTML>
<TITLE>Syria</TITLE>
<center>
<img src="milnetsm.gif" align=middle, alt="Milnet">
<p>
<p>
<a href="milnet.htm"><img src="milico.gif" align=middle alt="Milnet Main"></a>
<a href="military.htm"><img src="miltico.gif" align=middle alt="Military"></a>
<p>
<H1>Syria</H1>
</center>
<BR>
Syria is located just North of Jordon, within striking range of the major oil fields in the Middle East.  Syria has close ties to most 
of the pro-Soviet nations in the Middle East, and next to Iraq (previsu to the Gulf War), could be clasiffied as a major threat to 
the region in terms of military strength and politics.<BR>
	Syria shares borders with Israel, Lebanon, and Jordon, and is a known sanctuary for muslim fundamentalist terrorist 
groups.  PLO, PLFC, and other groups have both training camps and staging areas in Syria, and Israel is in a constant 
struggle to keep her common border clear.<P>
<img src="/milnet/note!sm.gif" align=middle>
The data below was verified in 1984.  Obviously it is obsolete.  We include
it here, however, as a measure of the forces available at that time.
We will endeavor to update that information as soon as we can given our
other goals for MILNET.
<p>

<H4><BR>
<BR>
Total Armed Forces:  362,500 (approx. 140,000 conscripts)<BR>
Def Budget: 1984:  $3.210 billion</H4>
<P>
<B>Army:  240,000</B> (120,000 conscripts, 50,000 reservists)<BR>
<BR>
4 armd divisions (each 2 armored, 1 mechanized brigade,l 1 is Presidential Guard unit)<BR>
4 mechanized divisions (east 1 armd, 2 mech bdes)<BR>
4 indep. mechanized brigades.<BR>
5 artillery brigades<BR>
9 paratroop/commando regiments.<BR>
3 SSM regiments:  1xScud, 1xFrog, 1xSS-21<BR>
102 SAM batterys with SA-2/3/6/8<BR>
<BR>
<B>AFV:</B>  1,800 T-44/55, 1,200 T-62, 1,100 T-72 Main Battle Tank; 200 BRDM recce/ATK vehicles; <BR>
   400 BMP MICV; 1,600 BTR-40/50/60/152, OT-64 Armored Personell Carrier<BR>
<B>Arty:</B>  2,700 2122mm (incl ISU-122 and M-1974 Self Propelled), M-46 130mm, M-1976 152mm and <BR>
   S-23 180mm guns; M-38, D-30 122mm, 152mm how incl M-1942 and M-1973 Self Propelled;<BR>
   M-21 122mm,   140mm, 240mm Multiple Rocket Launcher; 18 FROG-7, 12 SS-21, 18 SCUD SSM; <BR>
   120mm, 160mm,  240mm mortar.<BR>
<B>ATK:</B>  57mm, 85mm, 100mm guns; 1,300 Sagger, Spigot, and Milan ATGW<BR>
<B>AD:</B>  23mm, 37mm, 57mm towed, ZSU-23-4 ZSU-57-2 Self Propelled AA guns; SA-2/3/5/7/8/9 SAM<BR>
<P>
<B>Navy:  2,500</B><BR><B>
</B><BR>
2 Soviet Petra I class frigates<BR>
20 Soviet FAC(G) with Styx SSM; 6 Osa-I, 8 Osa-II; 6 Komar.<BR>
8 Soviet P-4 FAC(T).<BR>
1 French CH large patrol craft<BR>
