3 Soviet Zhuk coastal patrol craft.<BR>
On Order (1981): 4 Nanuchka II corvettes<BR>
<P>
<BR>
<B>Air Force:  70,000</B>   some 503 combat aircraft; some 90 armed helicopters<BR>
<BR>
11 FGA squadrons:  4 with MiG-17; 1 with 18 Su-7; 2 with 40 Su-20; 4 with 70 MiG23BM Flogger F.<BR>
12 interceptor squadrons; 2 with 50 MiG-25 Foxbat A; 10 with 200 MiG-21PF/MF; 40 MiG-233<BR>
    Flogger E.<BR>
2 tpt squadrons with 3 An-24, 4 An-26, 4 II-76, 8 II-14, 4 II-18, 2 Mystere 20F.<BR>
Trainers:  40 L-39, 60 K-29, 10 MiG-15UTI, 50 MBBB-223 Flamingo.<BR>
Helicopters:  10 Mi-2, 95 Mi-8, 30 Mi-24, 4 Ka-25 (ASW), 45 Gazelle (35 with ATGW)<BR>
AAM:  AA-2 Atoll<BR>
ASM:  AT-2 Swatter ATGW<BR>
On order:  12 Gazelle, 18 AB-212, 21 Super Frelon helicopters ;and various AAM<P>
<B>Paramilitary Forces:  38,000</B><BR><B>
</B><BR>
<B>Defence Companies:  25,000;  4 armd brigades</B><BR><B>
</B><BR>
<B>Gendarmerie:  8,000</B><BR><B>
</B><BR>
<B>Desert Guard (Frontier Force):  1,800</B><BR><B>
</B><BR>
<B>Palestine Liberation Army:  8,000 member brigades</B> and Syrian officers under PLO control<BR>
<BR>
90 T-54 Main Battle Tanks; 105mm, 122mm, 152mm howitzers;<BR>
Multiple Rocket Launchers, AT-3 Swagger ATGW; SA-7 SAM; <BR>
Workers Militia<P>
<P>
