<html>
<title>MILNET Military Information:  Taiwan</title>
<p>
<center>
<img align=middle src="milnetsm.gif">
<p>
<a href="milnet.htm"><img alt="Milnet Main" align=middle src="milico.gif"></a>
<a href="intell.htm"><img alt="Intell" align=middle src="intell.gif"></a>
<p>
<h1>Taiwan</h1>
</center>
<hr>
<b><i>Current information on Taiwan is being researched and is not yet available.  We apologize for the inconvience, especially during this period of activity 
between Taiwan and China.
</i></b>
<p>
<hr>

Taiwan
The country of Taiwan is a small set of islands off the coast of mainland China.  The Republic of China (ROC) as Taiwan was officially known until the 
mid-1990s, was formed by refugees from the Communist regime in mainland China.  
Since its formation, the small island chain has been a place of refuge from 
those fleeing from China, and a stepping stone to the western world.

<p>
Economically, Taiwan ranks second behind Japan in the Pacific Rim for its export
of electronic goods.  A major electronics player in the U.S., Taiwan continues 
to produce average quality goods at an excellent price, due to its extremely 
low labor costs.  Unlike Japan, the average citizen has not grown to enjoy 
expensive western culture, and the infrastructure of the country has not 
fostered the high cost of goods found in Japan.  For these reasons, Taiwan 
has the opportunity to overtake the Japanese as the economic leader in the 
Pacific Rim.
<p>
The Taiwan govenment maintains a small naval force which is primarily used to 
patrol the waters between her shores and that of Mainland China.  Any attack 
by the mainland China forces would quickly overwhelm Taiwan however.
<p>
<hr>
Last Updated:  12/1/87
</html>

