<HTML>
<TITLE>Fighter Aircraft</TITLE>
<H1>Fighter Aircraft</H1>
The modern fighter is used either as an air-superiority aircraft, or a surface (ground, anti-
ship, or anti-submarine) attack aircraft.   In many cases the aircraft will be designed for the 
anti-submarine or close air support role, or will be a dual role aircraft.<P>
Most surface attack aircraft are sub-sonic, since the need for supersonic speed is reduced 
for ground targeting.  But the dual role aircraft such as the Navy's F/A-18 may also be 
called upon to dump ordnance and engage the enemy in the air.<P>
Modern air-superiority fighters have max speeds in the Mach 1.8 to 2.3 range, and carry 
AAMs (infrared or radar guided).  See also  ATF .<P>
<P>
