<title>MILNET:  Recent Events Effecting Travellers</title>
<center>
<h1>Bosnia:  U.S. Foreign Service Employee Shot</h1>
</center>
<p>
A U.S. Foreign Service Employee, while driving back from a visit to Kiseljak
toward Sarejevo, was shot in the back by a passing motorist, according to 
Col Max Mariner.  However, U.S. Embasssy officials do not believe the attack
was politically motivated.

<p>
The randomness of the attack indiates, in our opinion a severe danger for all
foreign travellers in the region.  The recommendation is to simply avoid this
region of the world unless you are part of diplomatic or military missions
there, and of course travel under armed bodyguard protection.

<a href="http://travel.state.gov/bosnia-herzegovina.html">travel warning</a> for
Bosnia.

<p>
