<html>
<title>MILNET:  Travel Advisory</title>
<h1>MILNET:  Travel Advisory for Colombia</h1>
</center>
The U.S. Government has announced it is revoking the visa for Ernesto Samper,
the current President
of Colombia, prohibiting him from travelling into the U.S.
<p>
The action is a culminating event in the war against drugs in the U.S. and 
is symbolic of the U.S. frustration with cooperation with the Colombian
government. In the State Department decision, it was made clear the U.S. 
government believes Samper is tied to the drug cartels and that they helped
bankroll his election. 
<p>
U.S. citizens are warned that possible retalitory actions may be in planning,
and as such U.S. citizens may be at risk in that country.  Citizens are
urged to read the official U.S. 
<a href="http://travel.state.gov/colombia_announce3.html">
State Department Advisory</a> for travel in 
Columbia, which lists at least one other reason for caution.
<p>
<hr>
<a href="mailto:milnet@onestep.com"><i>milnet@onestep.com</i></a><br>

