<title>MILNET Military Information:  Japan MSDF</title>
<p>
<center>
<img align=middle src="milnetsm.gif">
<p>
<a href="milnet.htm"><img alt="Milnet Main" align=middle src="milico.gif"></a>
<a href="intell.htm"><img alt="Intell" align=middle src="intell.gif"></a>
<p>
<h1>Japan Maritime Self Defense Forces (MSDF)</h1>
</center>
<hr>

<p>
Japan's MSDF is tasked with keeping open the lanes with some 44,000 men and women.  The fleet has 14 attack submarines, 50 destroyers, 17 frigates, 46 amphibious craft, 37 mine warfare craft, and 14 small patrol combatants.
<p>

By the end of 1991 Japan will have a total of 60 destroyers.  Also, the MSDF operates 100 P-3C Orien aircraft, all assembled in Japan.  Japan will also be building three to four AEGIS class destroyers with the first in the class to be launched in 1991.
<p>

The naval airwing of 12,000 men includes 7 SAR fleets which include a number of aircraft and helicopters.
<p>

Destroyers are armed with ASROC, and the ASW frigates are armed with Harpoon.  The naval bases are located at Yokosuka, Kure, Sasebo, Maizuru, and Ominato.
<p>
<hr>
Last Updated:  12/1/87

