<title>MILNET Military Information:  Japan GSDF</title>
<p>
<center>
<img align=middle src="milnetsm.gif">
<p>
<a href="milnet.htm"><img alt="Milnet Main" align=middle src="milico.gif"></a>
<a href="intell.htm"><img alt="Intell" align=middle src="intell.gif"></a>
<p>
<h1>Japan Ground Self Defense Forces</h1>
</center>
<hr>
<p>

The ground forces feature over 150,000 combatants in 12 active divisions of between 7,000 and 9,000 troops each, and three composite brigades;1 armored division, and additional armored, helicopter, and airborne brigades.  The limit is 180,000.  The GSDF is divided into 5 Regional Commands.  The GSDF maintains around 1,200 main battle tanks, half of them the aging Type-61s, and including 156 Type 74 main battle tanks, as well as over 700 armored vehicles including 129 armored personnel carriers.  Japan plans on producing Type-90 THX tanks to replace the T-61s.
<p>
<ul>
<li>Artillery:   350 105mm, 394 155mm Self Propelled, 94 203mm, 800 81mm mortars, 560
107mm mortars, and 75 130mm self propelled multiple rocket launchers.
<li>AntiTank:  1,600 75 mm, 84mm, or 106mm recoiless.  228 Type 64, and 25 type 79 anti-tank
                guided weapon.
<li>Aviation:   21 LR-1, 2 Tl-1. 9 L-19, 2 AH-1S Cobra Gunships, 58 KV-107, 80 UH-1H Huey, 65
                UH-1B, 20 TH-55, 147 OH-6J/D helos.

<li>The GSDF also has a number of HAWK SAMS and Stinger.
</ul>
<p>
<hr>
Last Updated: 12/1/87
