<HTML>
<TITLE>Air to Ground Missiles (AGMs)</TITLE>
<center>
<img src="milnetsm.gif" align=middle, alt="Milnet">
<p>
<p>
<a href="milnet.htm"><img src="milico.gif" align=middle alt="Milnet Main"></a>
<a href="military.htm"><img src="miltico.gif" align=middle alt="Military"></a>
<p>
<p>
<H1>Air to Ground Missiles (AGMs)</H1>
</center>
AGMs are used in various air to surface roles, such as anti-tank attacks, attacks against 
ground force personnel, runways, or equipment. Included in this class of 
missiles are anti-shipping weapons..i.e. those weapons launched by aircraft i
upon surface or under-surface vessels, but excluding torpedoes.<P>
<H2>Legend</H2>
<pre>
<B>APMC</B>		Auto-Pilot with Mid-course Correction<P>
<B>ARG</B>		Active Radar Guided (typically guided by the aircraft all the way to target)<P>
<B>IG</B>		Inertial Guidance<P>
<B>IGMC</B>		Inertial Guidance, Mid-course Correction<P>
<B>IGTH</B>		Inertial Guidance, Terminal Homing (typically IIR or radar)<P>
<B>IGTM</B>		Inertial Guidance, Terrain Mapping (as standard in modern cruise missiles)<P>
<B>IGTVH</B>		Inertial Guidance, TV Homing<P>
<B>IIR</B>		Imaging InfraRed<P>
<B>LDLG</B>		Laser Designated, Laser Guided<P>
<B>LG</B>		Laser Guided<P>
<B>SARH</B>		Semi-Active Radar Homing<P>
<B>DUAL</B>		Both Laser and radar guided<P>
<B>PRAD</B>		Passive Radar homing (as in anti-radiation missiles)<P>
<B>RLTH</B>		Radar Lock, Terminal Homing<P>
<B>TV</B>		Magnifying Television image in cockpit<P>
<B>TVIIR</B>		Magnifying Television/Imaging InfraRed scanner<P>
<B>WIRE</B>		Wire guided to target<P>
<P>
<B>BF</B>		Blast Fragmentation<P>
<B>HE</B>		High Explosive<P>
<B>HEAT</B>		High Energy, very hot penetrating round<P>
<B>HEBF</B>		High Explosive, Blast Fragmentation<P>
<B>KE</B>		Kinetic Energy (high velocity penetrating rod explosive)<P>
<B>PHE</B>		Penetrating High Explosive<P>
<B>PR</B>		Penetrating Rod<P>
<B>UR</B>		Uranium rod (depleted uranium rod, very heavy mass, high velocity)<P>
<P>
<B>ALCM</B>		Air launched cruise missile<P>
<B>ARM</B>		Anti-Radiation Missile (seeks radar (or radio???) emitting targets)<P>
<B>ASM</B>		Anti-Shipping<P>
<B>ASW</B>		Anti-Submarine Warfare<P>
<B>ATW</B>		Anti-Tank Weapon<P>
<B>GA</B>		Ground Attack<P>
<B>HARM</B>		High Speed Anti-Radiation Missile<P>
<B>MRASM</B>		Medium Range Air-to-Surface-Missile<P>
<P>
