<TITLE>Director of Central Intelligence Directives</TITLE>
<center>
<img align=middle src="milnetsm.gif" alt="Milnet">
<p>
<p>
<a href="milnet.htm"><img alt="Milnet Main" align=middle src="milico.gif"></a>
<a href="intell.htm"><img alt="Intell" align=middle src="intell.gif"></a>
<p>
<p>
<B><H1>Director of Central Intelligence Directives</H1>
<p></center>
</B>DCIDs are assignments made by the DCI to various intelligence departments within the 
U.S. government.  The authority for the issuance of DCIDs comes from National Security 
Council Intelligence Directive (<a href="nscids.htm">NSCID</a>) No. 1 which details the DCIs responsiblities.  The 
following are examples of the subject matter of various DCIDs:<P>
<pre>
<b>Num	Description							Date</b>
<hr>
1/2    "U.S. Intelligence Requirements Categories and Priorities"	1/21/72
1/3    "Committees of the Director of Central Intelligence"		5/18/86
1/5    "Data Standardization for the Intelligence Community"		5/76
1/7    "Control of Dissemination of Intelligence Information  		5/4/81
1/8    "The National Foreign Intelligence Board"  (NFIB)   		5/6/76
        		 Updated version of 1/8 issued 			1/28/82
1/10  "Security Policy Guidance on Liaison Relationships with Foreign	1/18/82
		Intelligence Organizations and Foreign Security Services"
1/13  "Coordination of Collection and Exploitation of Imagery 		Date Unknown
		Intelligence"  		 


</pre><p>
<b>The following DCIDs deal with Security Standards:</b> <p>
<pre>
<b>Num	Description							Date</b>
<hr>
1/14  "Minimum Personnel Security Standards and Procedures Governing	4/14/86
         Eligibility for Access to Sensitive Compartmented Information."
1/16  "Security of Foreign Intelligence in Automated Data Processing	6/6/78
         Systems and Networks."
1/18  "Recognition of Exceptional Service to the U.S. Intelligence	5/18/76 
         Community."
