<TITLE>MILNET:  U.S. Intelligence - Presidential Directive of 1976</TITLE>
<center>
<img align=middle src="milnetsm.gif" alt="Milnet">
<p>
<p>
<a href="milnet.htm"><img alt="Milnet Main" align=middle src="milico.gif"></a>
<a href="intell.htm"><img alt="Intell" align=middle src="intell.gif"></a>
<p>
<p>
<H1>Presidential Directive of 1976</H1>
<p></center>
President Ford, in this Presidential Directive, established the 
Committee on Foreign Intelligence, reporting to the NSC Chairman, 
Kissinger, and with the DCI as the Chairman of this new committee.<P>
This directive also outlawed assassination as an instrument of American 
policy.<P>
This directive also (as each President does) outlines the CIAs domestic 
duties, and accepted the principle of a joint Congressional Oversight 
committee, however the Congress chose not to setup a joint committe, 
rather elected to each have their own committees.<P>
See also <a href="intauth.htm">Intelligence Authorization</a> of 1981.   <P>
