<a href="intell.htm"><img alt="Intell" align=middle src="intell.gif"></a>
<p>
<p>
<h1>MILNET:  Intelligence Agencies  by Function</h1>
</center>
<p>
Below we list the various intelligence agencies, grouped by the intelligence function they 
perform.  Note however, that in some cases the missions are sheer conjecture, since outside 
of the U.S., intelligence agency missions are not public knowlege.  Note too that even in 
the U.S. it is rumored that parts of the National Security Act remain classified.  This 
being the body of law that defines the activities of U.S. intelligence agencies, it is 
quite possible that the U.S. public is also unaware of certain missions of certain 
agencies.

Note also that this material originally was compiled prior to the breakup of the former 
Soviet Union, thus country names have not been changed to reflect modern renamings and 
borders (for instance East and West Germany are shown as separate countries).  Where 
former Soviet Union countries are shown, it is thought that the same organizations exist 
but under new names, and one would hope new management.
<p>
