<TITLE>MILNET:  U.S. Intelligence - NFIB</TITLE>
<center>
<img align=middle src="milnetsm.gif" alt="Milnet">
<p>
<p>
<a href="milnet.htm"><img alt="Milnet Main" align=middle src="milico.gif"></a>
<a href="intell.htm"><img alt="Intell" align=middle src="intell.gif"></a>
<p>
<H1>The National Foreign Intelligence Board</H1>
<p></center>
</B>The NFIB acts as a clearing house for all information gleaned by 
national intelligence assets on foreign powers.  This could very well 
include economic intelligence gathered via both covert or overt means.  
As with all organizations within the U.S. Intelligence Community, its 
existence may be only a front since being reported upon by various 
authors, having been replaced with another agency within the community.  
The name may have changed to the NFIC or National Foreign Intelligence 
Center.<P>
Source:  Richelson, <b><i><a href="biblio.htm#usintel">U.S. Intelligence Community</a></b></i>, and <b><i><a href="biblio.htm#secreteyes">America's Secret Eyes in the Sky</a></b></i>.
