<TITLE>MILNET:  U.S. Intelligence - NPIC</TITLE>
<center>
<img align=middle src="milnetsm.gif" alt="Milnet">
<p>
<p>
<a href="milnet.htm"><img alt="Milnet Main" align=middle src="milico.gif"></a>
<a href="intell.htm"><img alt="Intell" align=middle src="intell.gif"></a>
<p>
<H1>National Photographic Interpretation Center</H1>
<p></center>
The NPIC was originally formed to bring together national resources 
in order to ensure accurate and timely analysis and reporting on 
photographic imagery produced by national intelligence assets (read this 
as satellite and aircraft photographic imagery).  At the time of its 
formation, the concept of satellite imagery was so top secret that many 
interpreters did not know where the imagery was taken...or at least such 
speculation was discouraged.<P>
Today, the NPIC is thought to have been gobbled up and given over to the 
National Reconnaisance Office (NRO), and managed by the US Air Force 
under the auspices of the Undersecratery of the Air Force.<P>
(Source:  Richelson, <B><I>America's Secret Eyes In Space</B></I>, See 
<a href="biblio.htm#secreteyes">MILNET Bibliography</a>)<P>
