also printed seperately as "History of the Central Intelligence Agency", 
Anne Karalekas, Copyright 1977, Aegean Park Press, Laguna Hills, CA.   
Page 50.<P>
2.  Quoted as coming from "Souers interview", in <B><I>CIA and American 
Democracy</B></I>, Rhodri Jeffreys-Jones, Copyright 1989, Yale 
University Press, New Haven and London, Printed in the U.S. by Vail-
Ballou Press, Binghamton, New York.  ISBN 0-300-04149-7, Page 55.<P>
3.  Ibid, pg. 62<P>
4.  quoted in "<B><I>The CIA and the Intelligence Community</B></I>", 
Paul W. Blackstock, Copyright 1974, <P>
Forum Press, St. Charles, Mo. <P>
5.  <B><I>Viel: The Secret Wars of the CIA 1981-1987</B></I>, Bob 
